'''Eczema''' (From [[Ancient Greek language|Greek]] ''Ä“kzema'', 'to boil over') is a form of [[dermatitis]], or [[inflammation]] of the [[epidermis]] are the outer layer of the [[skin]].

A skin disease [[rash]]es itching and dryness, crusting, flaking, blistering, cracking, oozing, or bleeding. Areas of temporary skin discoloration may appear and are sometimes due to healed injuries.


